British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher'sConservatives lead the opposition Labour party by sevenpercentage points in the June 11 election campaign, accordingto a public opinion poll today.    The Harris poll on the TV-AM breakfast television show gaveThatcher's Conservative Party 42 pct, Labour 35 pct and thecentrist Alliance 21 pct.    This was a one point drop for the Conservatives and onepoint rise for the Alliance since the same organisation'ssurvey yesterday.    However, a Marplan poll in the Today newspaper had theConservatives 11 points ahead. It gave them 44 pct, Labour 33pct and the Alliance 21 pct.    All poll results since the campaign began have shown theConservatives in the lead. An aggregate of recent surveysshowed they held a nine to 10 point lead over Labour, enoughfor a comfortable election victory. REUTER&#3;